#: ../../docs/training_manual/spatial_databases/spatial_functions.rst:2
msgid "Lesson: PostGIS Setup"
msgstr "Lekcija: Podešavanje PostGIS-a"

#: ../../docs/training_manual/spatial_databases/spatial_functions.rst:4
msgid ""
"Setting up PostGIS functions will allow you to access spatial functions from"
" within PostgreSQL."
msgstr ""
"Podešavanje PostGIS funkcija će vam omogućiti pristup prostornim "
"funkcijama iz PostgreSQL-a."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/spatial_databases/spatial_functions.rst:7
msgid ""
"**The goal for this lesson:** To install spatial functions and briefly demo "
"their effects."
msgstr ""
"**Cilj ove lekcije:** Instalirati prostorne funkcije i ukratko demonstrirati"
" njihove efekte."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/spatial_databases/spatial_functions.rst:10
msgid ""
"We will assume the use of PostGIS version 2.1 or newer in this exercise. The"
" installation and database configuration are different for older versions, "
"but the rest of this material in this module will still work. Consult the "
"documentation for your platform for help with installation and database "
"configuration."
msgstr ""
"U ovoj vežbi pretpostavićemo upotrebu PostGIS verzije 2.1 ili novije. "
"Instalacija i konfiguracija baze podataka se razlikuju za starije verzije, "
"ali ostatak materijala u ovom modulu će i dalje funkcionisati. Za pomoć "
"oko instalacije i konfiguracije baze podataka pogledajte dokumentaciju za "
"vašu platformu."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/spatial_databases/spatial_functions.rst:17
msgid "Installing under Ubuntu"
msgstr "Instaliranje pod Ubuntuom"

#: ../../docs/training_manual/spatial_databases/spatial_functions.rst:19
msgid "Postgis is easily installed from apt."
msgstr "Postgis se lako instalira iz apt-a."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/spatial_databases/spatial_functions.rst:26
msgid "Really, it's that easy..."
msgstr "Zaista, to je tako lako..."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/spatial_databases/spatial_functions.rst:28
msgid ""
"The exact versions that will be installed depend on which version of Ubuntu "
"you are using and which repositories you have configured. After installing "
"you can check the version by issuing a ``select PostGIS_full_version();`` "
"query with psql or another tool."
msgstr ""
"Tačne verzije koje će biti instalirane zavise od toga koju verziju Ubuntua "
"koristite i koje ste repozitorijume konfigurisali. Nakon instalacije možete "
"proveriti verziju izdavanjem upita „select PostGIS_full_version();“ pomoću "
"psql-a ili nekog drugog alata."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/spatial_databases/spatial_functions.rst:32
msgid ""
"To install a specific version (eg, PostgreSQL version 13 and PostGIS 3), you"
" can use the following commands."
msgstr ""
"Da biste instalirali određenu verziju (npr. PostgreSQL verziju 13 i PostGIS "
"3), možete koristiti sledeće komande."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/spatial_databases/spatial_functions.rst:46
msgid "Installing under Windows"
msgstr "Instalacija na Windows-u"

#: ../../docs/training_manual/spatial_databases/spatial_functions.rst:48
msgid ""
"Installing on Windows can be done from binary packages using a normal "
"Windows installation dialogs."
msgstr ""
"Instalacija na Windows-u može se obaviti iz binarnih paketa pomoću "
"uobičajenih Windows dijaloga za instalaciju."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/spatial_databases/spatial_functions.rst:50
msgid ""
"First Visit `the download page <https://www.postgresql.org/download/>`_. "
"Then follow `this guide "
"<https://www.bostongis.com/PrinterFriendly.aspx?content_name=postgis_tut01>`_."
msgstr ""
"Prvo posetite `stranicu za preuzimanje "
"<https://www.postgresql.org/download/>`_. Zatim pratite `ovaj vodič "
"<https://www.bostongis.com/PrinterFriendly.aspx?content_name=postgis_tut01>`_."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/spatial_databases/spatial_functions.rst:53
msgid ""
"More information about installing on Windows can be found on the `PostGIS "
"website <https://postgis.net/documentation/getting_started/>`_."
msgstr ""
"Više informacija o instalaciji na Windows-u možete pronaći na `PostGIS sajtu"
" <https://postgis.net/documentation/getting_started/>`_."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/spatial_databases/spatial_functions.rst:57
msgid "Installing on Other Platforms"
msgstr "Instalacija na drugim platformama"

#: ../../docs/training_manual/spatial_databases/spatial_functions.rst:59
msgid ""
"The `PostGIS website download "
"<https://postgis.net/documentation/getting_started/>`_ has information about"
" installing on other platforms including macOS and on other Linux "
"distributions"
msgstr ""
"`Preuzimanje sa PostGIS sajta "
"<https://postgis.net/documentation/getting_started/>`_ sadrži informacije o "
"instalaciji na drugim platformama, uključujući macOS i druge Linux "
"distribucije"

#: ../../docs/training_manual/spatial_databases/spatial_functions.rst:64
msgid "Configuring Databases to use PostGIS"
msgstr "Konfigurisanje baza podataka za korišćenje PostGIS-a"

#: ../../docs/training_manual/spatial_databases/spatial_functions.rst:66
msgid ""
"Once PostGIS is installed, you will need to configure your database to use "
"the extensions. If you have installed PostGIS version > 2.0, this is as "
"simple as issuing the following command with psql using the address database"
" from our previous exercise."
msgstr ""
"Kada je PostGIS instaliran, potrebno je da konfigurišete svoju bazu podataka"
" da koristi ekstenzije. Ako ste instalirali PostGIS verziju > 2.0, ovo je "
"jednostavno kao izdavanje sledeće komande pomoću psql koristeći bazu "
"podataka address iz naše prethodne vežbe."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/spatial_databases/spatial_functions.rst:75
msgid ""
"Depending on your version, you could find more instructions on how to "
"spatially enable a database at "
"https://postgis.net/docs/postgis_administration.html#create_spatial_db."
msgstr ""
"U zavisnosti od vaše verzije, više uputstava o tome kako prostorno omogućiti"
" bazu podataka možete pronaći na "
"https://postgis.net/docs/postgis_administration.html#create_spatial_db."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/spatial_databases/spatial_functions.rst:80
msgid "Looking at the installed PostGIS functions"
msgstr "Pregled instaliranih PostGIS funkcija"

#: ../../docs/training_manual/spatial_databases/spatial_functions.rst:82
msgid ""
"PostGIS can be thought of as a collection of in-database functions that "
"extend the core capabilities of PostgreSQL so that it can deal with spatial "
"data. By 'deal with', we mean store, retrieve, query and manipulate. In "
"order to do this, a number of functions are installed into the database."
msgstr ""
"PostGIS se može zamisliti kao zbirka funkcija unutar baze podataka koje "
"proširuju osnovne mogućnosti PostgreSQL-a tako da može da radi sa prostornim"
" podacima. Pod „radi sa“ mislimo na čuvanje, preuzimanje, postavljanje upita"
" i manipulaciju. Da bi se to postiglo, u bazu podataka se instalira niz "
"funkcija."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/spatial_databases/spatial_functions.rst:87
msgid ""
"Our PostgreSQL ``address`` database is now geospatially enabled, thanks to "
"PostGIS. We are going to delve a lot deeper into this in the coming "
"sections, but let's give you a quick little taster. Let's say we want to "
"create a point from text. First we use the psql command to find functions "
"relating to point. If you are not already connected to the ``address`` "
"database, do so now. Then run:"
msgstr ""
"Naša PostgreSQL ``address`` baza podataka sada je geoprostorno omogućena, "
"zahvaljujući PostGIS-u. U ovo ćemo mnogo dublje zaroniti u narednim "
"odeljcima, ali dajmo vam kratku probu. Recimo da želimo da napravimo tačku "
"iz teksta. Prvo koristimo psql komandu da pronađemo funkcije koje se odnose "
"na tačku. Ako već niste povezani sa ``address`` bazom podataka, povežite se "
"sada. Zatim pokrenite:"

#: ../../docs/training_manual/spatial_databases/spatial_functions.rst:97
msgid ""
"This is the command we're looking for: ``st_pointfromtext``.  To page "
"through the list, use the down arrow, then press :kbd:`Q` to quit back to "
"the psql shell."
msgstr ""
"Ovo je komanda koju tražimo: ``st_pointfromtext``. Za listanje kroz listu "
"koristite strelicu nadole, zatim pritisnite :kbd:`Q` da biste izašli nazad u"
" psql školjku."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/spatial_databases/spatial_functions.rst:100
msgid "Try running this command:"
msgstr "Pokušajte da pokrenete ovu komandu:"

#: ../../docs/training_manual/spatial_databases/spatial_functions.rst:106
#: ../../docs/training_manual/spatial_databases/spatial_functions.rst:140
#: ../../docs/training_manual/spatial_databases/spatial_functions.rst:207
msgid "Result:"
msgstr "Rezultat:"

#: ../../docs/training_manual/spatial_databases/spatial_functions.rst:115
msgid "Three things to note:"
msgstr "Tri stvari koje treba primetiti:"

#: ../../docs/training_manual/spatial_databases/spatial_functions.rst:117
msgid ""
"We defined a point at position 1,1 (EPSG:4326 is assumed) using ``POINT(1 "
"1)``,"
msgstr ""
"Definisali smo tačku na položaju 1,1 (pretpostavlja se EPSG:4326) pomoću "
"``POINT(1 1)``,"

#: ../../docs/training_manual/spatial_databases/spatial_functions.rst:119
msgid ""
"We ran an sql statement, but not on any table, just on data entered from the"
" SQL prompt,"
msgstr ""
"Pokrenuli smo sql naredbu, ali ne nad bilo kojom tabelom, već samo nad "
"podacima unetim iz SQL prompta,"

#: ../../docs/training_manual/spatial_databases/spatial_functions.rst:121
msgid "The resulting row does not make much sense."
msgstr "Rezultujući red nema mnogo smisla."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/spatial_databases/spatial_functions.rst:123
msgid ""
"The resulting row is in the OGC format called 'Well Known Binary' (WKB). We "
"will look at this format in detail in the next section."
msgstr ""
"Rezultujući red je u OGC formatu pod nazivom „Well Known Binary“ (WKB). Ovaj"
" format ćemo detaljno razmotriti u sledećem odeljku."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/spatial_databases/spatial_functions.rst:126
msgid ""
"To get the results back as text, we can do a quick scan through the function"
" list for something that returns text:"
msgstr ""
"Da bismo rezultate dobili nazad kao tekst, možemo brzo pregledati listu "
"funkcija za nešto što vraća tekst:"

#: ../../docs/training_manual/spatial_databases/spatial_functions.rst:133
msgid ""
"The query we're looking for now is ``st_astext``. Let's combine it with the "
"previous query:"
msgstr ""
"Upit koji sada tražimo je ``st_astext``. Kombinujmo ga sa prethodnim upitom:"

#: ../../docs/training_manual/spatial_databases/spatial_functions.rst:149
msgid ""
"Here, we entered the string ``POINT(1,1)``, turned it into a point using "
"``st_pointfromtext()``, and turned it back into a human-readable form with "
"``st_astext()``, which gave us back our original string."
msgstr ""
"Ovde smo uneli nisku ``POINT(1,1)``, pretvorili je u tačku pomoću "
"``st_pointfromtext()``, i pretvorili je nazad u čitljiv oblik pomoću "
"``st_astext()``, što nam je vratilo našu originalnu nisku."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/spatial_databases/spatial_functions.rst:154
msgid ""
"One last example before we really get into the detail of using PostGIS:"
msgstr ""
"Još jedan poslednji primer pre nego što zaista uđemo u detalje korišćenja "
"PostGIS-a:"

#: ../../docs/training_manual/spatial_databases/spatial_functions.rst:160
msgid ""
"What did that do? It created a buffer of 1 degree around our point, and "
"returned the result as text."
msgstr ""
"Šta je to uradilo? Napravilo je bafer od 1 stepena oko naše tačke i vratilo "
"rezultat kao tekst."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/spatial_databases/spatial_functions.rst:164
msgid "Spatial Reference Systems"
msgstr "Prostorni referentni sistemi"

#: ../../docs/training_manual/spatial_databases/spatial_functions.rst:166
msgid ""
"In addition to the PostGIS functions, the extension contains a collection of"
" spatial reference system (SRS) definitions as defined by the European "
"Petroleum Survey Group (EPSG). These are used during operations such as "
"coordinate reference system (CRS) conversions."
msgstr ""
"Pored PostGIS funkcija, ekstenzija sadrži zbirku definicija prostornih "
"referentnih sistema (SRS) kako ih je definisala Evropska grupa za naftna "
"istraživanja (EPSG). Ove se koriste tokom operacija kao što su pretvaranja "
"koordinatnih referentnih sistema (CRS)."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/spatial_databases/spatial_functions.rst:171
msgid ""
"We can inspect these SRS definitions in our database as they are stored in "
"normal database tables."
msgstr ""
"Ove SRS definicije možemo pregledati u našoj bazi podataka jer su sačuvane u"
" običnim tabelama baze podataka."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/spatial_databases/spatial_functions.rst:174
msgid ""
"First, let's look at the schema of the table by entering the following "
"command in the psql prompt:"
msgstr "Prvo, pogledajmo šemu tabele unosom sledeće komande u psql prompt:"

#: ../../docs/training_manual/spatial_databases/spatial_functions.rst:181
msgid "The result should be this:"
msgstr "Rezultat treba da bude ovo:"

#: ../../docs/training_manual/spatial_databases/spatial_functions.rst:196
msgid ""
"You can use standard SQL queries (as we have learned from our introductory "
"sections), to view and manipulate this table - though its not a good idea to"
" update or delete any records unless you know what you are doing."
msgstr ""
"Možete koristiti standardne SQL upite (kao što smo naučili iz naših uvodnih "
"odeljaka) za pregled i manipulaciju ovom tabelom - mada nije dobra ideja "
"ažurirati ili brisati bilo koje zapise osim ako ne znate šta radite."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/spatial_databases/spatial_functions.rst:200
msgid ""
"One SRID you may be interested in is EPSG:4326 - the geographic / lat lon "
"reference system using the WGS 84 ellipsoid. Let's take a look at it:"
msgstr ""
"Jedan SRID koji vas može zanimati je EPSG:4326 - geografski / lat lon "
"referentni sistem koji koristi WGS 84 elipsoid. Pogledajmo ga:"

#: ../../docs/training_manual/spatial_databases/spatial_functions.rst:221
msgid ""
"The ``srtext`` is the projection definition in well known text (you may "
"recognise this from .prj files in your shapefile collection)."
msgstr ""
"``srtext`` je definicija projekcije u dobro poznatom tekstu (možda ćete ga "
"prepoznati iz .prj datoteka u svojoj zbirci shapefile-ova)."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/spatial_databases/spatial_functions.rst:225
msgid "In Conclusion"
msgstr "Zaključak"

#: ../../docs/training_manual/spatial_databases/spatial_functions.rst:227
msgid ""
"You now have PostGIS functions installed in your copy of PostgreSQL. With "
"this you'll be able to make use of PostGIS' extensive spatial functions."
msgstr ""
"Sada imate PostGIS funkcije instalirane u svojoj kopiji PostgreSQL-a. Sa "
"ovim ćete moći da koristite obimne prostorne funkcije PostGIS-a."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/spatial_databases/spatial_functions.rst:231
msgid "What's Next?"
msgstr "Šta je sledeće?"

#: ../../docs/training_manual/spatial_databases/spatial_functions.rst:233
msgid "Next you'll learn how spatial features are represented in a database."
msgstr ""
"Zatim ćete naučiti kako se prostorni objekti predstavljaju u bazi podataka."
